âš ï¸ This is global, affects all threads â†’ avoid in production.

5ï¸âƒ£ Using without_callback (ActiveSupport hacky)

Not officially supported, avoid.

6ï¸âƒ£ Custom flag to bypass callback (BEST PRACTICE)
Model
class User < ApplicationRecord
  attr_accessor :skip_callbacks

  before_save :normalize_email, unless: :skip_callbacks

  def normalize_email
    self.email = email.downcase
  end
end

Usage
user.skip_callbacks = true
user.save


âœ… Safe
âœ… Explicit
âœ… Thread-safe

7ï¸âƒ£ Why skipping callbacks is dangerous ğŸš¨

Callbacks often:

Send emails

Update counters

Sync external services

Enforce business rules

Skipping them can:

Corrupt data

Break invariants

Cause silent bugs

Interview-ready summary ğŸ¯

Yes, Rails allows skipping callbacks using methods like update_column, update_all, or by explicitly guarding callbacks with flags. However, skipping callbacks should be done carefully because callbacks often contain critical business logic.

